Make a huge impact at a highly successful e-learning software company. As Manager or Director of HR, you will own and drive Articulate&rsquo;s HR programs. You will help with a broad range of HR activities including recruiting, on-boarding, and ongoing people training and management tasks. You will work with the company&rsquo;s management team in establishing the right policies and procedures mitigating corporate risk and working to continue Articulate&rsquo;s amazing company culture. You will drive the adoption of company benefits programs and manage and maintain these programs. This position reports to the COO and is a work-from-home position.</p>
<p>
An ideal candidate has significant experience building and managing HR programs at high-growth technology companies. Candidates must be great HR partners with clear perspectives on HR programs while being flexible based on business needs. You should be highly detail oriented and able to work with a high degree of autonomy and independence. You should be a great advocate for employees and representative of the company and its culture.</p>
<br />
<p>
Responsibilities:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Drive recruiting activities and manage relationships with third-party recruiters</li>
<li>
Drive selection and management of key HR benefit programs including health care, 401K, transportation, health and wellness, vacation, etc.</li>
<li>
Manage onboarding process with new hires</li>
<li>
Advise company management on HR policies and procedures</li>
<li>
Partner with company employees to provide HR support activities</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li>
5+ of years experience as an HR leader</li>
<li>
Previous experience building and managing HR team</li>
<li>
Outstanding people skills</li>
<li>
Prefer experience having worked in a recruiting capacity</li>
<li>
Superior skills working in a high-growth, nimble organization working with online and cloud-based systems.</li>
</ul>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Our business:</p>
