<strong>Sr. Analyst&mdash;Marketing Analytics &amp; Research</strong></p>
<p>
Articulate is looking for a senior analyst of marketing analytics to join our new digital marketing team. You&rsquo;ll report directly to the VP of digital marketing and have a huge impact on our business. As a key member of the digital marketing team, you&rsquo;ll be responsible for organizing, maintaining, extracting, and analyzing marketing data from databases and other sources. You&rsquo;ll then present business performance, identifying issues and opportunities.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop forecasts, present current performance, develop testing matrices for campaigns, and research opportunities and concerns in partnership with marketing team</li>
<li>
Work with VP of digital marketing to create a central data warehouse, monitor databases, and ensure data quality</li>
<li>
Establish and manage a reporting framework and dashboards to educate business partners on performance relevant to their areas of work</li>
<li>
Perform statistical analysis using techniques such as regression analysis, multivariate analysis, choice-based conjoint, analysis of variance (ANOVA), and data mining</li>
<li>
Develop complex, high-visibility direct marketing campaigns (utilizing marketing tools and applications) through partnership with other departments; develop data segmentation strategies that drive marketing campaigns; and ensure test and learn techniques are properly executed, including test cell structure and sample size calculations</li>
<li>
Organize and present findings regarding market trends, competitive intelligence, customer preferences, and market penetration strategies; make recommendations to address issues</li>
<li>
Take the lead to manage moderately complex research or analytic projects that involve multiple team members</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent, with 5 years of related experience</li>
<li>
Advanced business degree preferred</li>
<li>
Experience with primary, secondary, and database analysis research methodologies</li>
<li>
Experience with marketing and sales platforms (e.g. Salesforce, Adwords, Google Analytics)</li>
<li>
Knowledge of SQL desirable</li>
<li>
Strong proficiency in PC-based spreadsheets</li>
<li>
Strong quantitative analysis, problem solving, and project management skills</li>
<li>
Excellent written and verbal communication skills</li>
